<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id5288054c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s608"><num value="608">§ 608.</num><heading> Seal</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director shall use a seal approved by the Supreme Court. Judicial notice shall be taken of such seal.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id5288054d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/915">62 Stat. 915</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id5288054e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id5288054f-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 444 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s302">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 302</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/act/1939-08-07/ch501/s1">Aug. 7, 1939, ch. 501, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/53/1223">53 Stat. 1223</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This section contains a part of <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s444">section 444 of title 28</ref>, U.S.C., 1940 ed. The remainder of said section 444 is incorporated in sections 601, 603 and 606 of this title.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes were made in phraseology.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
